org.nd4j.resources.strumpf

Class StrumpfResolver

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.nd4j.resources.strumpf.StrumpfResolver
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Resolver

    public class StrumpfResolver
extends Object
implements Resolver
    Resource resources based on Strumpf resource files, or standard files
    https://github.com/deeplearning4j/strumpf
    Note that resource files (those with path ending with REF) point to remote files, that will be downloaded, decompressed and cached locally.
    The default cache location is DEFAULT_CACHE_DIR; this can be overridden by setting the ND4JSystemProperties#RESOURCES_CACHE_DIR system property.


    Two resolution methods are supported:
    1. Resolving from the classpath
    2. Resolving from one of any specified directories

    Resolving from specified directories: You can point this to one or more local directories (rather than relying on classpath) when resolving resources. This can be done by setting the ND4JSystemProperties.RESOURCES_LOCAL_DIRS
    Author:
    Alex Black
